column5: By now i would think you guys there're finnished having a Ceasar and tearing into a box of Blue.I sure wished I could help you EH!
Yeah, Happy Canada Day, eh? Bill

It's hard to beat a good Ceasar, but when the cocktail hour rolls around today, it will be time for a Rusty Nail. Moose on the menu tonight, but the cook informed me that the walleye caught today will be for lunch tomorrow. A little warm for my liking, but overall a good Canada day, enjoy your 4th of July!
It's good to be here on Eagle Lake on Canada Day....take it away Tom...https://www.bing.com/videos/search?q...1A48A2D4523857

First time in almost thirty years that I've not spent Canada Day in Canada.First time in nearly thirty years that I've actually been home for the fourth of July fireworks, but there are none.Strange times we are all sharing together.Pooch

So this year you will know if it is actually knee high by the 4th of July? If it makes you feel any better the temps are too hot this week up here anyway, you don't even need a sweatshirt in the mornings.
Happy Day and you guys are the best, demonstrated by how you handle a crisis-adapt, improvise, and overcome.
Happy Canada day to all my Canadian friends!

Hot up there too! No wonder you're inside on the confuser this time of day. Chest and shoulder high. Few if any tassels by the fourth. There are a lot of replant acres that might be about knee high by the fourth. No Black flies or May flies here... Don't miss 'em. Pooch
